flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Weekly MPS run (scheduled) or event-driven when demand forecast, capacity, or supplier lead-time data changes beyond thresholds.]
  A --> N1[Stream: DDM/Crawlers - Ingest master data, orders, forecasts, capacities, and supplier lead-times from SAP S/4HANA]
  N1 --> N2[Stream: STREAMS - Transform, validate, and store planning datasets into Subject Areas; run data quality checks]
  N2 --> N3{PB: Remote Functions (optimization solver) - Orchestrate optimization run that solves multi-horizon, multi-echelon scheduling and allocations}
  N3 -->|Primary| N4[PB: Remote Functions - Write optimized schedules and allocation decisions back to SAP S/4HANA and publish Subject Area outputs]
  N4 --> N5[PB: UI Screen - Surface schedule, KPIs, and exception flags to planners; monitor performance and COGS impact]
  N5 --> N6[PB: Cortex Monitoring - Track forecast accuracy, schedule adherence, and optimization metrics over time]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Automatically generated, executable production schedules that reduce COGS, eliminate schedule conflicts, increase line efficiency, and improve on-time delivery; measurable reductions in production cost and inventory carrying, with KPIs tracked in Cortex Monitoring.]
  N3 -->|Solver returns infeasible solution du...| B1[Process Builder triggers Branch - Rules to relax non-critical constraints or kick-off CWB Lifecycle exception for planner intervention with suggested relaxations]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Manual or rule-driven constraint relaxation produces a feasible schedule; exception logged and escalated if unresolved]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Optimized schedule increases projecte...| B2[Route to CWB Lifecycle for planner review with cost/compliance trade-off report and alternative candidate schedules]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Planner accepts alternative or approves optimized plan with justification; decision recorded for governance]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Data quality checks fail (missing or ...| B3[Process Builder invokes Notification + Data View report to data steward and pauses downstream optimization until remediation]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Data corrected and re-ingested; optimization re-run once integrity is restored]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]